fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
A set N is called a natural number set if it is equipped with

an element 0 \in  N;

a successor function s\colon N\to N.
  These data are subject to the following requirements.

s\colon N\to N is injective;

non-looping: for every x \in  N, s(x) \neq  0;

induction principle: for every set P \subseteq  N, if 0 \in  P and for all x \in  N, x \in  P implies that s(x) \in  P then P = N.
